title: Local sports briefs for Oct. 7: KU volleyball notches another sweep to remain perfect
text:
Local sports briefs for Oct. 7: KU volleyball notches another sweep to remain perfect K-State falls in straight sets to Iowa State Posted: October 7, 2015 - 10:53pm By The Capital-Journal 
The Kansas volleyball team earned its third straight sweep in Big 12 play Wednesday, brushing aside Texas Tech 25-21, 25-14, 25-20 in Lubbock, Texas. 
The No. 10 Jayhawks (16-0, 4-0) recorded more digs (51-50), assists (49-38), blocks (5-1) and kills (50-41) over the three sets, with Kelsie Payne pacing KU with a game-high 17 kills. Cassie Watt contributed 16 digs, while Ainise Havili had 41 kills. 
KU will look to remain unbeaten when it hosts Iowa State at 4 p.m. Saturday in Lawrence. 
CYCLONES SWEEP WILDCATS IN AMES: The Kansas State volleyball team was swept Wednesday by Iowa State 25-22, 25-20, 25-20 in Ames, Iowa. 
Jess Schaben and Morgan Kuhrt had a team-high nine kills for the Cyclones, who hit .179 as a team. Katie Reininger had a match-high 10 kills for the Wildcats (9-7, 1-3).
